<br>
On the other hand, there are quite a few classes who can not solo, who must rely on groups; when we are off soloing, we are depriving those who must group of necessary classes.  This weakens their ability to gain experience, and in many cases the resolve to continue with these necessary classes.  So an enchanter can solo a PoP mini-boss.  So a bard can solo some summoning dragons.  Doesn't make much of a difference when we can't do anything bigger with a group because of the missing or inexperienced (read: PL'd) key classes.<br>
<br>
/shrug<br>
<br>
I'm a part time player, who doesn't have the time to do 4-5 hour exp sessions.  That makes the ability to use the time I do have to gain significant experience invaluable to me - to stay with the rest of my friends in game.  As a result, I am able to keep joining groups which I might not otherwise be able to join.<br>
<br>
Whether I am able to continue with my soloing abilities will depend greatly on the changes to Charm which have hit the test servers.  Either way, I shall adapt, and continue to do the most important thing - enjoy this game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=astyd>astyd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#330000>(3/26/03 10:13:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=128.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: cannot be serious......</span><hr size=1> I have tried charming many times in PoP and its quite doable, especially with snare items.  I think that attacking Tier 3 mini-bosses even with Command of Druzzil will be tough.  Please note that CoD has been changed to lower its resist adjust.  Thus, its no longer &quot;unresistable&quot;.<br>
